<HEADING>NetBSD FTP mirror FAQ

<LIST>

<SECTION>Becoming a NetBSD FTP mirror site

<ENTRY>steps  What steps should I take to be a NetBSD FTP mirror site?
<OL>
<LI>Prepare disk space.  See <a href="#diskspace">below</a> for the ammount required.
<LI>Inform <mirrors@netbsd.org> of the mirror server, with contact information
	in the specified format.
<LI>Synchronize the content with the master server.
<LI>Maintain the server.  Synchronize periodically.
</OL>

<ENTRY>diskspace  How much disk space do I need to prepare?
Full mirror would require around 34G as of Feb 2001.

<ENTRY>contactinfo  Tell me about contact information format.
Contact information must be submitted to <mirrors@netbsd.org> in the
following format:

<PRE>
mirror		*machine name*
country		*location (country) of host*
location	*more specific location (e.g, ``University of Foo'')*
ftp		*FTP URL*
ftp-host	*external FTP name*
organisation	*organisation name*
contactperson	*contact person's name*
contactemail	*contact person's electronic mail address*
contactphone	*contact person's telephone number*
contactaddress	*contact person's postal address*
</PRE>

A template would be like this.

<PRE>
mirror		ftp.foo-univ.ac.jp
country		Japan
location	Department of Computer Science, Foo University
ftp		ftp://ftp.foo-univ.ac.jp/pub/NetBSD/
ftp-host	ftp.foo-univ.ac.jp
organisation	Foo University
contactperson	Foo Bar
contactemail	Bar@foo-univ.ac.jp
contactphone	+81 3 xxxx yyyy
contactaddress	9876 Foo City, Tokyo 1234567 Japan
</PRE>

<ENTRY>domain  Is it possible to get a DNS name under "netbsd.org" tree?
It is possible to point your machine as ftp.country-code.netbsd.org, like
ftp.jp.netbsd.org.
We do not normally do subdomain delegation,
so you cannot run a nameserver for "country-code.netbsd.org".

<SECTION>Babysitting

<ENTRY>requirement  What is necessary for a mirror maintainer?
Synchronize FTP tree regularly.  Otherwise, old and/or obsolete files
may confuse users.
<p>
Sometimes, due to security issue or other issues, file removal may be
requested from the project.
Please take necessary action quickly, in this case.
<p>

